The Telegraph - Calcutta : International
 Friday, April 09, 2004 				 Shia interior minister quits
				 	 Nouri Badran																								Baghdad, April 8 (Reuters): Iraqi interior minister Nouri Badran resigned today, saying he had heard that the US-led administration was unhappy with his performance and wanted a different religious mix in the cabinet.																								Badran, a Shia, said he had been told by Paul Bremer, the US administrator of Iraq, that the defence minister and interior minister should not both be Shias. A new defence ministers position was created this month and filled by a Shia official. 
